Responded to 51-74% of applications in the past 30 days, typically within 1 day.

Our Client supports: (1) core development projects; and (2) entrepreneurs and their enterprises. It does this by: (1) hosting a blockchain research and development team that builds software to strengthen the client's ecosystem; and (2) hosting up to 25 startups annually, providing investment, mentorship, office space, and support.

We are looking for a Project Manager to join a team of developers working to strengthen the Ethereum Classic blockchain. This person will manage the relevance, delivery, and community oriented interfaces of the team’s strategic roadmap and projects.

Specifically, the Project Manager will have the following responsibilities:
• Collaborate with developers to define and manage work plans;
• Inform project strategy and plans with customer/user preferences, usability, and needs to ensure relevance and adoption;
• Engage with the client and other communities and key stakeholders to increase adoption and reach of products;
• Conduct industry and customer/user research to identify trends and opportunities for our client;
• Help to ensure on-time delivery of high-quality, relevant products.
• Experience in the technology industry, preferably with startup environments;
• Familiarity with and/or interest in blockchain development and cryptocurrency;
• Ability to collaborate with teams of developers;
• Planning and project management skills; * Ability to engage with a range stakeholders;
• Familiarity (though not necessarily proficiency) with programming languages and computer science, with a preference for distributed systems.

• Research new and upcoming changes and trends in the blockchain-based technical field;
• Maintain documentation and guides for using and connecting to TRON's blockchain network;
• Establish and maintain the environments in which blockchain solutions can be implemented, including development, testing, and production environments;
• Travel to China occasionally to work with the team in person.
• Willing to / Able to research and implement cutting-edge blockchain technology;
• Good at one or more of these languages: Java, Go, or C/C++;
• Comfortable in a multinational startup, especially working with China, environment;
• Experience in the development of blockchain technology;
• Experience with development on other blockchains, ie Ethereum;

